Program: The Forum
Title: Measuring Impact
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01hnv96
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 7 Oct 2013
Measuring is embedded into everything we do from our personal achievements to profits and losses. But has it become an obsession? Or are we measuring the wrong things? How can you measure trust for example? To discuss the results, Carrie Gracie talks to Mike McCreless who invests in rural businesses in developing countries, academic economist Rocco Macchiavello, who has been looking at trust in the work place and clinical psychologist Oliver James. (Picture: Computer screen showing a graph. Credit: Nicky Barranger) Show less